This paper focuses on the analysis of social media conversations and the spread of rumours, which falls under the categories of social media (cs.SOC) and computational linguistics (cs.CL). The study also involves the use of machine learning techniques to assess the veracity of rumours, which falls under the categories of cybersecurity (cs.CYBER) and cryptography and security (cs.CR). Finally, the methodology used in the study involves the collection and annotation of a dataset, which falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
